Note:
Runa Standard Library: Core Configuration Management Module

Provides comprehensive configuration management capabilities that integrate environment
variables, configuration files, secrets, and hierarchical configuration merging.
This module serves as the unified interface for all configuration needs in Runa
applications, supporting development, staging, and production environments.

Features:
- Unified configuration interface combining multiple sources
- Hierarchical configuration with precedence rules
- Type-safe configuration access with validation
- Configuration schema definition and enforcement
- Dynamic configuration reloading and hot-swapping
- Configuration interpolation and templating
- Environment-specific configuration profiles
- Configuration caching and performance optimization
- Comprehensive audit logging and change tracking
- Integration with secrets management for sensitive data
- Configuration migration and versioning support
- AI-friendly configuration patterns for agent systems

Configuration Sources (in precedence order):
1. Command-line arguments and runtime overrides
2. Environment variables with prefix filtering
3. Local configuration files (.runa.yaml, .runa.json, etc.)
4. User-specific configuration files
5. System-wide configuration files
6. Default configuration values from schema

Security Features:
- Sensitive value detection and masking
- Secure configuration transmission
- Configuration encryption for sensitive environments
- Access control and permission validation
- Audit trail for all configuration changes

Thread Safety: All configuration operations are thread-safe and designed
for high-concurrency applications with minimal performance overhead.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/config/environment" as environment
Import "stdlib/config/loader" as loader
Import "stdlib/config/secrets" as secrets

Note: Core Configuration Types and Structures
Type ConfigurationProfile is:
    | DEVELOPMENT
    | TESTING
    | STAGING
    | PRODUCTION
    | CUSTOM with name as String

Type called "ConfigurationSource":
    source_id as String
    source_type as String
    source_path as Optional[String] defaults to None
    priority as Integer defaults to 0
    enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    required as Boolean defaults to false
    environment_prefix as Optional[String] defaults to None
    file_format as Optional[loader.ConfigFormat] defaults to None
    reload_enabled as Boolean defaults to false
    reload_interval as Float defaults to 60.0
    last_loaded as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    last_modified as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    load_count as Integer defaults to 0
    error_count as Integer defaults to 0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ConfigurationValue":
    key as String
    value as Any
    data_type as String
    source as String
    priority as Integer
    last_updated as Float
    access_count as Integer defaults to 0
    sensitive as Boolean defaults to false
    encrypted as Boolean defaults to false
    validated as Boolean defaults to false
    interpolated as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ConfigurationSchema":
    schema_version as String defaults to "1.0"
    schema_id as String
    required_keys as List[String] defaults to list containing
    optional_keys as List[String] defaults to list containing
    key_types as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    key_constraints as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to dictionary containing
    default_values as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    sensitive_keys as List[String] defaults to list containing
    validation_rules as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    key_descriptions as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    migration_rules as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to dictionary containing
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "Configuration":
    config_id as String
    profile as ConfigurationProfile
    values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] defaults to dictionary containing
    sources as List[ConfigurationSource] defaults to list containing
    schema as Optional[ConfigurationSchema] defaults to None
    creation_timestamp as Float
    last_reload as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    last_validation as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    auto_reload_enabled as Boolean defaults to false
    auto_reload_interval as Float defaults to 300.0
    cache_enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    cache_ttl as Float defaults to 600.0
    audit_enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ConfigurationOptions":
    profile as ConfigurationProfile defaults to DEVELOPMENT
    auto_discover_files as Boolean defaults to true
    discovery_paths as List[String] defaults to list containing
    environment_prefix as Optional[String] defaults to None
    enable_secrets_integration as Boolean defaults to false
    secrets_store as Optional[secrets.SecretStore] defaults to None
    strict_mode as Boolean defaults to false
    enable_interpolation as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_validation as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_caching as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_file_watching as Boolean defaults to false
    enable_audit_logging as Boolean defaults to true
    performance_monitoring as Boolean defaults to false
    max_cache_size as Integer defaults to 1000
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type ConfigurationResult[T] is:
    | ConfigurationSuccess with value as T and source as String and metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | ConfigurationMissing with key as String and searched_sources as List[String]
    | ConfigurationInvalid with key as String and error_message as String and value as Any
    | ConfigurationException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type called "ConfigurationChange":
    change_id as String
    change_type as String
    key as String
    old_value as Optional[Any] defaults to None
    new_value as Any
    source as String
    timestamp as Float
    triggered_by as String
    validation_passed as Boolean defaults to true
    propagated as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Core Configuration Management Functions
Process called "create_configuration" that takes options as Optional[ConfigurationOptions] returns Configuration:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_options be options if options is not None else create_default_configuration_options
    Let config_id be generate_configuration_id
    
    Try:
        Note: Create base configuration structure
        Let configuration be Configuration with:
            config_id as config_id
            profile as final_options.profile
            values as dictionary containing
            sources as list containing
            schema as None
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            last_reload as None
            last_validation as None
            auto_reload_enabled as final_options.enable_file_watching
            auto_reload_interval as 300.0
            cache_enabled as final_options.enable_caching
            cache_ttl as 600.0
            audit_enabled as final_options.enable_audit_logging
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "load_count" as 0
                "reload_count" as 0
                "cache_hits" as 0
                "cache_misses" as 0
                "validation_count" as 0
                "error_count" as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "created_with_options" as final_options
                "version" as "1.0"
        
        Note: Auto-discover configuration sources if enabled
        If final_options.auto_discover_files:
            Let discovery_result be discover_configuration_sources with:
                search_paths as final_options.discovery_paths
                profile as final_options.profile
                options as final_options
            
            For each discovered_source in discovery_result.sources:
                Add discovered_source to configuration.sources
        
        Note: Add environment variable source
        Let env_source be ConfigurationSource with:
            source_id as "environment_variables"
            source_type as "environment"
            source_path as None
            priority as 100
            enabled as true
            required as false
            environment_prefix as final_options.environment_prefix
            file_format as None
            reload_enabled as true
            reload_interval as 30.0
            last_loaded as None
            last_modified as None
            load_count as 0
            error_count as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing "auto_added" as true
        
        Add env_source to configuration.sources
        
        Note: Load initial configuration
        Let load_result be load_configuration_from_sources with:
            configuration as configuration
            options as final_options
        
        If load_result.success:
            log_configuration_event with:
                config_id as config_id
                event_type as "CONFIGURATION_CREATED"
                details as dictionary containing:
                    "profile" as final_options.profile as String
                    "sources_count" as length of configuration.sources
                    "values_count" as length of configuration.values
        
        Return configuration
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Configuration creation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "load_configuration_from_sources" that takes configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let loading_errors be list containing
    Let loaded_values be dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Sort sources by priority (higher priority loads last to override)
        Let sorted_sources be sort_sources_by_priority with sources as configuration.sources
        
        For each source in sorted_sources:
            If not source.enabled:
                Continue
            
            Let source_load_result be load_from_single_source with:
                source as source
                configuration as configuration
                options as options
            
            Match source_load_result.status:
                When "success":
                    Note: Merge loaded values with priority handling
                    For each key, value in source_load_result.values:
                        Let config_value be ConfigurationValue with:
                            key as key
                            value as value
                            data_type as determine_data_type with value as value
                            source as source.source_id
                            priority as source.priority
                            last_updated as current_time
                            access_count as 0
                            sensitive as is_sensitive_configuration_key with key as key
                            encrypted as false
                            validated as false
                            interpolated as false
                            metadata as dictionary containing "loaded_from" as source.source_type
                        
                        Note: Apply precedence rules
                        If loaded_values contains key:
                            Let existing_value be loaded_values[key]
                            If source.priority is greater than existing_value.priority:
                                Set loaded_values[key] to config_value
                        Otherwise:
                            Set loaded_values[key] to config_value
                    
                    Set source.last_loaded to current_time
                    Set source.load_count to source.load_count plus 1
                
                When "error":
                    Add source_load_result.error_message to loading_errors
                    Set source.error_count to source.error_count plus 1
                    
                    If source.required:
                        Return dictionary containing:
                            "success" as false
                            "error_message" as "Required source failed to load: " plus source_load_result.error_message
                
                When "not_found":
                    If source.required:
                        Return dictionary containing:
                            "success" as false
                            "error_message" as "Required source not found: " plus source.source_path as String
        
        Note: Apply post-processing
        Let processed_values be post_process_configuration_values with:
            values as loaded_values
            configuration as configuration
            options as options
        
        Note: Update configuration with loaded values
        Set configuration.values to processed_values
        Set configuration.last_reload to current_time
        Set configuration.performance_metrics["load_count"] to configuration.performance_metrics["load_count"] plus 1
        
        Note: Validate configuration if enabled
        If options.enable_validation and configuration.schema is not None:
            Let validation_result be validate_configuration_against_schema with:
                configuration as configuration
                schema as configuration.schema
            
            Set configuration.last_validation to current_time
            Set configuration.performance_metrics["validation_count"] to configuration.performance_metrics["validation_count"] plus 1
            
            If not validation_result.valid and options.strict_mode:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as "Configuration validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "loaded_count" as length of processed_values
            "errors" as loading_errors
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Configuration loading exception: " plus error.message

Process called "get_configuration_value" that takes configuration as Configuration and key as String and default_value as Optional[Any] and data_type as Optional[String] returns ConfigurationResult[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if key exists in configuration
        If configuration.values contains key:
            Let config_value be configuration.values[key]
            
            Note: Update access tracking
            Set config_value.access_count to config_value.access_count plus 1
            
            Note: Handle encrypted values
            If config_value.encrypted:
                Let decryption_result be decrypt_configuration_value with:
                    config_value as config_value
                    configuration as configuration
                
                If not decryption_result.success:
                    Return ConfigurationException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to decrypt configuration value: " plus decryption_result.error_message
                        error_code as "DECRYPTION_ERROR"
                
                Return ConfigurationSuccess with:
                    value as decryption_result.decrypted_value
                    source as config_value.source
                    metadata as dictionary containing:
                        "encrypted" as true
                        "access_count" as config_value.access_count
                        "last_updated" as config_value.last_updated
            
            Note: Apply type conversion if requested
            If data_type is not None and data_type is not equal to config_value.data_type:
                Let conversion_result be convert_configuration_value with:
                    value as config_value.value
                    target_type as data_type
                    key as key
                
                If not conversion_result.success:
                    Return ConfigurationInvalid with:
                        key as key
                        error_message as "Type conversion failed: " plus conversion_result.error_message
                        value as config_value.value
                
                Return ConfigurationSuccess with:
                    value as conversion_result.converted_value
                    source as config_value.source
                    metadata as dictionary containing:
                        "type_converted" as true
                        "original_type" as config_value.data_type
                        "target_type" as data_type
                        "access_count" as config_value.access_count
            
            Note: Log access for sensitive values
            If config_value.sensitive and configuration.audit_enabled:
                log_configuration_event with:
                    config_id as configuration.config_id
                    event_type as "SENSITIVE_VALUE_ACCESSED"
                    details as dictionary containing:
                        "key" as key
                        "source" as config_value.source
                        "access_count" as config_value.access_count
            
            Return ConfigurationSuccess with:
                value as config_value.value
                source as config_value.source
                metadata as dictionary containing:
                    "data_type" as config_value.data_type
                    "sensitive" as config_value.sensitive
                    "access_count" as config_value.access_count
                    "last_updated" as config_value.last_updated
        
        Note: Key not found, check for default value
        If default_value is not None:
            Return ConfigurationSuccess with:
                value as default_value
                source as "default"
                metadata as dictionary containing:
                    "used_default" as true
                    "requested_key" as key
        
        Note: No value found and no default
        Let searched_sources be list containing
        For each source in configuration.sources:
            If source.enabled:
                Add source.source_id to searched_sources
        
        Return ConfigurationMissing with:
            key as key
            searched_sources as searched_sources
    
    Catch error:
        Return ConfigurationException with:
            error_message as "Configuration value retrieval exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "RETRIEVAL_EXCEPTION"

Process called "set_configuration_value" that takes configuration as Configuration and key as String and value as Any and source as Optional[String] and metadata as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_source be source if source is not None else "runtime"
    Let final_metadata be metadata if metadata is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if this is an update or new value
        Let is_update be configuration.values contains key
        Let old_value be If is_update then configuration.values[key].value else None
        
        Note: Validate value if schema exists
        If configuration.schema is not None:
            Let validation_result be validate_single_configuration_value with:
                key as key
                value as value
                schema as configuration.schema
            
            If not validation_result.valid:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as "Value validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                    "error_code" as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Encrypt value if it's sensitive
        Let should_encrypt be is_sensitive_configuration_key with key as key
        Let final_value be value
        Let encrypted as Boolean be false
        
        If should_encrypt and final_metadata contains "encrypt" and final_metadata["encrypt"]:
            Let encryption_result be encrypt_configuration_value with:
                value as value
                configuration as configuration
            
            If encryption_result.success:
                Set final_value to encryption_result.encrypted_value
                Set encrypted to true
            Else:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as "Value encryption failed: " plus encryption_result.error_message
                    "error_code" as "ENCRYPTION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Create configuration value object
        Let config_value be ConfigurationValue with:
            key as key
            value as final_value
            data_type as determine_data_type with value as value
            source as final_source
            priority as 999  Note: Runtime values have highest priority
            last_updated as current_time
            access_count as 0
            sensitive as should_encrypt
            encrypted as encrypted
            validated as true
            interpolated as false
            metadata as final_metadata
        
        Note: Store the value
        Set configuration.values[key] to config_value
        
        Note: Create change record
        Let change be ConfigurationChange with:
            change_id as generate_change_id
            change_type as If is_update then "update" else "create"
            key as key
            old_value as old_value
            new_value as value
            source as final_source
            timestamp as current_time
            triggered_by as "runtime_set"
            validation_passed as true
            propagated as false
            metadata as final_metadata
        
        Note: Log the change
        If configuration.audit_enabled:
            log_configuration_change with:
                config_id as configuration.config_id
                change as change
        
        Note: Notify change listeners if any
        notify_configuration_change with:
            configuration as configuration
            change as change
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "change_id" as change.change_id
            "is_update" as is_update
            "encrypted" as encrypted
            "sensitive" as should_encrypt
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Configuration value set exception: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "SET_EXCEPTION"

Process called "reload_configuration" that takes configuration as Configuration and options as Optional[ConfigurationOptions] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_options be options if options is not None else create_default_configuration_options
    
    Try:
        Note: Store current values for comparison
        Let previous_values be deep_copy_configuration_values with values as configuration.values
        
        Note: Clear current values
        Set configuration.values to dictionary containing
        
        Note: Reload from all sources
        Let reload_result be load_configuration_from_sources with:
            configuration as configuration
            options as final_options
        
        If not reload_result.success:
            Note: Restore previous values on failure
            Set configuration.values to previous_values
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Configuration reload failed: " plus reload_result.error_message
                "values_restored" as true
        
        Note: Compare values and generate change events
        Let changes be compare_configuration_values with:
            old_values as previous_values
            new_values as configuration.values
        
        Note: Update metrics
        Set configuration.performance_metrics["reload_count"] to configuration.performance_metrics["reload_count"] plus 1
        Set configuration.last_reload to current_time
        
        Note: Log reload event
        If configuration.audit_enabled:
            log_configuration_event with:
                config_id as configuration.config_id
                event_type as "CONFIGURATION_RELOADED"
                details as dictionary containing:
                    "changes_count" as length of changes
                    "reload_time" as current_time
                    "sources_count" as length of configuration.sources
        
        Note: Notify listeners of changes
        For each change in changes:
            notify_configuration_change with:
                configuration as configuration
                change as change
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "changes_count" as length of changes
            "values_count" as length of configuration.values
            "reload_time" as current_time
            "changes" as changes
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Configuration reload exception: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "RELOAD_EXCEPTION"

Process called "validate_configuration" that takes configuration as Configuration and schema as Optional[ConfigurationSchema] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_schema be schema if schema is not None else configuration.schema
    
    If final_schema is None:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as true
            "warnings" as list containing "No schema provided for validation"
            "errors" as list containing
    
    Try:
        Let validation_errors be list containing
        Let validation_warnings be list containing
        
        Note: Check required keys
        For each required_key in final_schema.required_keys:
            If not configuration.values contains required_key:
                Add "Required key missing: " plus required_key to validation_errors
        
        Note: Validate each configuration value
        For each key, config_value in configuration.values:
            Let value_validation be validate_single_configuration_value with:
                key as key
                value as config_value.value
                schema as final_schema
            
            If not value_validation.valid:
                Add "Key '" plus key plus "': " plus value_validation.error_message to validation_errors
            
            If length of value_validation.warnings is greater than 0:
                For each warning in value_validation.warnings:
                    Add "Key '" plus key plus "': " plus warning to validation_warnings
        
        Note: Check for unknown keys if strict mode
        If final_schema.metadata contains "strict_mode" and final_schema.metadata["strict_mode"]:
            Let all_known_keys be final_schema.required_keys plus final_schema.optional_keys
            For each key, config_value in configuration.values:
                If not all_known_keys contains key:
                    Add "Unknown key in strict mode: " plus key to validation_warnings
        
        Note: Update validation tracking
        Set configuration.last_validation to current_time
        Set configuration.performance_metrics["validation_count"] to configuration.performance_metrics["validation_count"] plus 1
        
        Let is_valid be length of validation_errors is equal to 0
        
        If configuration.audit_enabled:
            log_configuration_event with:
                config_id as configuration.config_id
                event_type as "CONFIGURATION_VALIDATED"
                details as dictionary containing:
                    "valid" as is_valid
                    "errors_count" as length of validation_errors
                    "warnings_count" as length of validation_warnings
                    "schema_id" as final_schema.schema_id
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as is_valid
            "errors" as validation_errors
            "warnings" as validation_warnings
            "schema_id" as final_schema.schema_id
            "validation_time" as current_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as false
            "errors" as list containing "Validation exception: " plus error.message
            "warnings" as list containing
            "validation_time" as current_time

Process called "get_configuration_profile" that takes configuration as Configuration returns ConfigurationProfile:
    Return configuration.profile

Process called "get_configuration_sources" that takes configuration as Configuration returns List[ConfigurationSource]:
    Return configuration.sources

Process called "get_configuration_metadata" that takes configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "config_id" as configuration.config_id
        "profile" as configuration.profile as String
        "values_count" as length of configuration.values
        "sources_count" as length of configuration.sources
        "creation_timestamp" as configuration.creation_timestamp
        "last_reload" as configuration.last_reload
        "last_validation" as configuration.last_validation
        "auto_reload_enabled" as configuration.auto_reload_enabled
        "cache_enabled" as configuration.cache_enabled
        "audit_enabled" as configuration.audit_enabled
        "performance_metrics" as configuration.performance_metrics
        "schema_id" as If configuration.schema is not None then configuration.schema.schema_id else None
:End Note

Note: Configuration Source Discovery and Management
Process called "discover_configuration_sources" that takes search_paths as List[String] and profile as ConfigurationProfile and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let discovered_sources be list containing
    Let discovery_errors be list containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Define common configuration file patterns
        Let file_patterns be list containing:
            "config", "runa", "settings", "app", "application"
        
        Let extensions be list containing:
            ".json", ".yaml", ".yml", ".toml", ".ini", ".env"
        
        Note: Search each path
        For each search_path in search_paths:
            For each pattern in file_patterns:
                For each extension in extensions:
                    Note: Try profile-specific files first
                    Let profile_specific_name be pattern plus "." plus profile as String plus extension
                    Let profile_specific_path be search_path plus "/" plus profile_specific_name
                    
                    If file_exists with path as profile_specific_path:
                        Let source be ConfigurationSource with:
                            source_id as "file_" plus profile_specific_name
                            source_type as "file"
                            source_path as profile_specific_path
                            priority as calculate_file_priority with profile as profile and pattern as pattern
                            enabled as true
                            required as false
                            environment_prefix as None
                            file_format as detect_format_from_extension with path as profile_specific_path
                            reload_enabled as options.enable_file_watching
                            reload_interval as 60.0
                            last_loaded as None
                            last_modified as None
                            load_count as 0
                            error_count as 0
                            metadata as dictionary containing:
                                "discovered" as true
                                "profile_specific" as true
                                "pattern" as pattern
                        
                        Add source to discovered_sources
                    
                    Note: Try generic files
                    Let generic_name be pattern plus extension
                    Let generic_path be search_path plus "/" plus generic_name
                    
                    If file_exists with path as generic_path:
                        Let source be ConfigurationSource with:
                            source_id as "file_" plus generic_name
                            source_type as "file"
                            source_path as generic_path
                            priority as calculate_file_priority with profile as profile and pattern as pattern minus 10
                            enabled as true
                            required as false
                            environment_prefix as None
                            file_format as detect_format_from_extension with path as generic_path
                            reload_enabled as options.enable_file_watching
                            reload_interval as 60.0
                            last_loaded as None
                            last_modified as None
                            load_count as 0
                            error_count as 0
                            metadata as dictionary containing:
                                "discovered" as true
                                "profile_specific" as false
                                "pattern" as pattern
                        
                        Add source to discovered_sources
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "sources" as discovered_sources
            "discovery_errors" as discovery_errors
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "sources" as discovered_sources
            "discovery_errors" as list containing error.message

Process called "load_from_single_source" that takes source as ConfigurationSource and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match source.source_type:
            When "file":
                Return load_from_file_source with:
                    source as source
                    configuration as configuration
                    options as options
            
            When "environment":
                Return load_from_environment_source with:
                    source as source
                    configuration as configuration
                    options as options
            
            When "secrets":
                Return load_from_secrets_source with:
                    source as source
                    configuration as configuration
                    options as options
            
            When "remote":
                Return load_from_remote_source with:
                    source as source
                    configuration as configuration
                    options as options
            
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "error"
                    "error_message" as "Unknown source type: " plus source.source_type
                    "values" as dictionary containing
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "Source loading exception: " plus error.message
            "values" as dictionary containing

Process called "load_from_file_source" that takes source as ConfigurationSource and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If source.source_path is None:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "File source path is null"
            "values" as dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Let loader_options be loader.create_default_loader_options
        Set loader_options.enable_interpolation to options.enable_interpolation
        Set loader_options.strict_mode to options.strict_mode
        Set loader_options.enable_caching to options.enable_caching
        
        Let load_result be loader.load_configuration_file with:
            path as source.source_path
            format as source.file_format
            options as loader_options
        
        Match load_result:
            When loader.LoadSuccess:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "success"
                    "values" as load_result.data
                    "load_metadata" as dictionary containing:
                        "format" as load_result.format as String
                        "load_time" as load_result.load_time
                        "source_file" as load_result.source_file
            
            When loader.LoadError:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "error"
                    "error_message" as load_result.error_message
                    "values" as dictionary containing
            
            When loader.LoadPartial:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "success"
                    "values" as load_result.data
                    "warnings" as load_result.errors
                    "load_metadata" as dictionary containing:
                        "partial_load" as true
                        "source_file" as load_result.source_file
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "File source loading exception: " plus error.message
            "values" as dictionary containing

Process called "load_from_environment_source" that takes source as ConfigurationSource and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let env_values be environment.get_all_environment_variables with:
            prefix_filter as source.environment_prefix
            include_sensitive as false
        
        Let processed_values be dictionary containing
        
        For each env_name, env_value in env_values:
            Note: Convert environment variable name to configuration key
            Let config_key be normalize_environment_key_to_config_key with:
                env_name as env_name
                prefix as source.environment_prefix
            
            Note: Convert value based on detected type
            Let converted_value be convert_environment_value_to_config_type with:
                value as env_value
                key as config_key
            
            Set processed_values[config_key] to converted_value
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "success"
            "values" as processed_values
            "load_metadata" as dictionary containing:
                "source_type" as "environment"
                "prefix_filter" as source.environment_prefix
                "values_count" as length of processed_values
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "Environment source loading exception: " plus error.message
            "values" as dictionary containing

Process called "load_from_secrets_source" that takes source as ConfigurationSource and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If not options.enable_secrets_integration:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "Secrets integration is disabled"
            "values" as dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Load secrets that match configuration pattern
        Let secrets_values be dictionary containing
        
        Note: Get list of secrets that should be loaded
        If source.metadata contains "secret_keys":
            Let secret_keys be source.metadata["secret_keys"]
            
            For each secret_key in secret_keys:
                Let secret_result be secrets.get_secret with:
                    secret_id as secret_key
                    store as options.secrets_store
                
                Match secret_result:
                    When secrets.SecretSuccess:
                        Set secrets_values[secret_key] to secret_result.value
                    
                    When secrets.SecretNotFound:
                        If options.strict_mode:
                            Return dictionary containing:
                                "status" as "error"
                                "error_message" as "Required secret not found: " plus secret_key
                                "values" as dictionary containing
                    
                    Otherwise:
                        If options.strict_mode:
                            Return dictionary containing:
                                "status" as "error"
                                "error_message" as "Secret access failed: " plus secret_key
                                "values" as dictionary containing
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "success"
            "values" as secrets_values
            "load_metadata" as dictionary containing:
                "source_type" as "secrets"
                "secrets_count" as length of secrets_values
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "Secrets source loading exception: " plus error.message
            "values" as dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Configuration Processing and Utilities
Process called "post_process_configuration_values" that takes values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue]:
    Let processed_values be deep_copy_configuration_values with values as values
    
    Try:
        Note: Apply interpolation if enabled
        If options.enable_interpolation:
            Let interpolation_result be apply_configuration_interpolation with:
                values as processed_values
                configuration as configuration
            
            If interpolation_result.success:
                Set processed_values to interpolation_result.interpolated_values
        
        Note: Mark values as processed
        For each key, config_value in processed_values:
            Set config_value.interpolated to options.enable_interpolation
            Set config_value.validated to false  Note: Will be validated separately if needed
        
        Return processed_values
    
    Catch error:
        Return values  Note: Return original values on processing error

Process called "apply_configuration_interpolation" that takes values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let interpolated_values be deep_copy_configuration_values with values as values
        Let interpolation_context be build_interpolation_context with configuration as configuration
        
        For each key, config_value in interpolated_values:
            If is_string with value as config_value.value:
                Let interpolated_result be interpolate_configuration_string with:
                    template as config_value.value
                    context as interpolation_context
                    configuration as configuration
                
                If interpolated_result.success:
                    Set config_value.value to interpolated_result.interpolated_value
                    Set config_value.interpolated to true
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "interpolated_values" as interpolated_values
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Interpolation exception: " plus error.message

Process called "build_interpolation_context" that takes configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let context be dictionary containing
    
    Note: Add all configuration values as potential interpolation sources
    For each key, config_value in configuration.values:
        If not config_value.sensitive:  Note: Don't expose sensitive values in interpolation
            Set context[key] to config_value.value as String
    
    Note: Add environment variables
    Let env_vars be environment.get_all_environment_variables with:
        prefix_filter as None
        include_sensitive as false
    
    For each env_name, env_value in env_vars:
        Set context["env." plus env_name] to env_value
    
    Note: Add system information
    Set context["profile"] to configuration.profile as String
    Set context["config_id"] to configuration.config_id
    
    Return context

Process called "validate_configuration_against_schema" that takes configuration as Configuration and schema as ConfigurationSchema returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return validate_configuration with:
        configuration as configuration
        schema as schema

Process called "validate_single_configuration_value" that takes key as String and value as Any and schema as ConfigurationSchema returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let validation_errors be list containing
        Let validation_warnings be list containing
        
        Note: Check if key is known
        Let all_known_keys be schema.required_keys plus schema.optional_keys
        If not all_known_keys contains key:
            Add "Unknown configuration key" to validation_warnings
        
        Note: Check type if specified
        If schema.key_types contains key:
            Let expected_type be schema.key_types[key]
            Let actual_type be determine_data_type with value as value
            
            If expected_type is not equal to actual_type:
                Add "Type mismatch. Expected: " plus expected_type plus ", got: " plus actual_type to validation_errors
        
        Note: Apply constraints if specified
        If schema.key_constraints contains key:
            Let constraints be schema.key_constraints[key]
            Let constraint_result be apply_value_constraints with:
                value as value
                constraints as constraints
                key as key
            
            If not constraint_result.valid:
                Add constraint_result.error_message to validation_errors
        
        Note: Apply custom validation rules if specified
        If schema.validation_rules contains key:
            Let validation_rule be schema.validation_rules[key]
            Let custom_validation_result be apply_custom_validation_rule with:
                value as value
                rule as validation_rule
                key as key
            
            If not custom_validation_result.valid:
                Add custom_validation_result.error_message to validation_errors
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as length of validation_errors is equal to 0
            "errors" as validation_errors
            "warnings" as validation_warnings
            "error_message" as If length of validation_errors is greater than 0 then validation_errors[0] else ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as false
            "errors" as list containing "Validation exception: " plus error.message
            "warnings" as list containing
            "error_message" as "Validation exception: " plus error.message

Process called "convert_configuration_value" that takes value as Any and target_type as String and key as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match target_type:
            When "string":
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as true
                    "converted_value" as value as String
            
            When "integer":
                Let int_result be parse_integer_from_string with value as value as String
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as int_result.success
                    "converted_value" as int_result.value
                    "error_message" as int_result.error_message
            
            When "float":
                Let float_result be parse_float_from_string with value as value as String
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as float_result.success
                    "converted_value" as float_result.value
                    "error_message" as float_result.error_message
            
            When "boolean":
                Let bool_result be parse_boolean_from_string with value as value as String
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as bool_result.success
                    "converted_value" as bool_result.value
                    "error_message" as bool_result.error_message
            
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "converted_value" as value
                    "error_message" as "Unsupported target type: " plus target_type
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "converted_value" as value
            "error_message" as "Conversion exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_configuration_options" returns ConfigurationOptions:
    Return ConfigurationOptions with:
        profile as DEVELOPMENT
        auto_discover_files as true
        discovery_paths as list containing ".", "./config", "./configs", "/etc/runa", "~/.runa"
        environment_prefix as None
        enable_secrets_integration as false
        secrets_store as None
        strict_mode as false
        enable_interpolation as true
        enable_validation as true
        enable_caching as true
        enable_file_watching as false
        enable_audit_logging as true
        performance_monitoring as false
        max_cache_size as 1000
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "generate_configuration_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_part be generate_random_string with length as 8
    Return "config_" plus timestamp as String plus "_" plus random_part

Process called "generate_change_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_part be generate_random_string with length as 6
    Return "change_" plus timestamp as String plus "_" plus random_part

Process called "sort_sources_by_priority" that takes sources as List[ConfigurationSource] returns List[ConfigurationSource]:
    Note: Sort sources by priority (ascending order so higher priority overrides)
    Let sorted_sources be list containing
    Let temp_sources be copy_list with lst as sources
    
    Note: Simple bubble sort implementation for priority ordering
    Let n be length of temp_sources
    For i from 0 to n minus 1:
        For j from 0 to n minus i minus 2:
            If temp_sources[j].priority is greater than temp_sources[j plus 1].priority:
                Let temp be temp_sources[j]
                Set temp_sources[j] to temp_sources[j plus 1]
                Set temp_sources[j plus 1] to temp
    
    Return temp_sources

Process called "is_sensitive_configuration_key" that takes key as String returns Boolean:
    Let sensitive_patterns be list containing:
        "password", "secret", "key", "token", "credential", "auth",
        "private", "api_key", "access_token", "refresh_token"
    
    Let lowercase_key be lowercase of key
    
    For each pattern in sensitive_patterns:
        If lowercase_key contains pattern:
            Return true
    
    Return false

Process called "determine_data_type" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Determine data type of configuration value based on actual type inspection
    If value is None:
        Return "null"
    Otherwise if is_boolean with value as value:
        Return "boolean"
    Otherwise if is_integer with value as value:
        Return "integer"
    Otherwise if is_float with value as value:
        Return "float"
    Otherwise if is_list with value as value:
        Return "list"
    Otherwise if is_dictionary with value as value:
        Return "dictionary"
    Otherwise:
        Return "string"

Process called "calculate_file_priority" that takes profile as ConfigurationProfile and pattern as String returns Integer:
    Let base_priority be 50
    
    Note: Higher priority for profile-specific files
    Let profile_bonus be 20
    
    Note: Pattern-based priorities
    Let pattern_priority be Match pattern:
        When "config":
            10
        When "runa":
            15
        When "settings":
            5
        When "app":
            8
        When "application":
            8
        Otherwise:
            0
    
    Return base_priority plus profile_bonus plus pattern_priority

Process called "detect_format_from_extension" that takes path as String returns loader.ConfigFormat:
    Return loader.detect_config_format with path as path

Process called "file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists at path using OS file system checks
    Try:
        Let file_info be get_file_info with path as path
        Return file_info.exists
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "normalize_environment_key_to_config_key" that takes env_name as String and prefix as Optional[String] returns String:
    Let processed_name be env_name
    
    Note: Remove prefix if specified
    If prefix is not None and env_name starts with prefix:
        Set processed_name to substring of env_name from length of prefix to length of env_name
    
    Note: Convert to lowercase and replace underscores with dots
    Let config_key be lowercase of processed_name
    Set config_key to replace_string with:
        text as config_key
        old_substring as "_"
        new_substring as "."
    
    Return config_key

Process called "convert_environment_value_to_config_type" that takes value as String and key as String returns Any:
    Note: Try to auto-detect and convert types
    If value is equal to "true" or value is equal to "false":
        Return value is equal to "true"
    
    Note: Try integer conversion
    Let int_result be parse_integer_from_string with value as value
    If int_result.success:
        Return int_result.value
    
    Note: Try float conversion
    Let float_result be parse_float_from_string with value as value
    If float_result.success:
        Return float_result.value
    
    Note: Return as string
    Return value

Process called "deep_copy_configuration_values" that takes values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] returns Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue]:
    Let copied_values be dictionary containing
    For each key, config_value in values:
        Note: Create deep copy of ConfigurationValue
        Let copied_config_value be ConfigurationValue with:
            key as config_value.key
            value as deep_copy_value with value as config_value.value
            data_type as config_value.data_type
            source as config_value.source
            priority as config_value.priority
            last_updated as config_value.last_updated
            access_count as config_value.access_count
            sensitive as config_value.sensitive
            encrypted as config_value.encrypted
            validated as config_value.validated
            interpolated as config_value.interpolated
            metadata as deep_copy_dictionary with d as config_value.metadata
        
        Set copied_values[key] to copied_config_value
    Return copied_values

Process called "deep_copy_value" that takes value as Any returns Any:
    Note: Deep copy a value preserving its structure
    If value is None:
        Return None
    Otherwise if is_dictionary with value as value:
        Return deep_copy_dictionary with d as value
    Otherwise if is_list with value as value:
        Return deep_copy_list with lst as value
    Otherwise:
        Note: Primitive values are copied by value
        Return value

Process called "deep_copy_dictionary" that takes d as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns Dictionary[Any, Any]:
    Let result be dictionary containing
    For each key, value in d:
        Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    Return result

Process called "deep_copy_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Add deep_copy_value with value as item to result
    Return result

Process called "compare_configuration_values" that takes old_values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] and new_values as Dictionary[String, ConfigurationValue] returns List[ConfigurationChange]:
    Let changes be list containing
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Note: Check for removed values
    For each key, old_value in old_values:
        If not new_values contains key:
            Let change be ConfigurationChange with:
                change_id as generate_change_id
                change_type as "remove"
                key as key
                old_value as old_value.value
                new_value as None
                source as "reload"
                timestamp as current_time
                triggered_by as "configuration_reload"
                validation_passed as true
                propagated as false
                metadata as dictionary containing
            
            Add change to changes
    
    Note: Check for added or modified values
    For each key, new_value in new_values:
        If old_values contains key:
            Let old_value be old_values[key]
            If not old_value.value is equal to new_value.value:
                Let change be ConfigurationChange with:
                    change_id as generate_change_id
                    change_type as "update"
                    key as key
                    old_value as old_value.value
                    new_value as new_value.value
                    source as new_value.source
                    timestamp as current_time
                    triggered_by as "configuration_reload"
                    validation_passed as true
                    propagated as false
                    metadata as dictionary containing
                
                Add change to changes
        Otherwise:
            Let change be ConfigurationChange with:
                change_id as generate_change_id
                change_type as "add"
                key as key
                old_value as None
                new_value as new_value.value
                source as new_value.source
                timestamp as current_time
                triggered_by as "configuration_reload"
                validation_passed as true
                propagated as false
                metadata as dictionary containing
            
            Add change to changes
    
    Return changes

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch with microsecond precision
    Let time_info be get_system_time
    Return time_info.timestamp_seconds plus time_info.microseconds divided by 1000000.0

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random string for IDs and security purposes
    Let characters be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789"
    Let result be ""
    
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        Let random_index be generate_secure_random_integer with max as length of characters
        Let random_char be character_at with text as characters and index as random_index
        Set result to result plus random_char
    
    Return result

Process called "lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Convert string to lowercase using Unicode-aware conversion
    Let result be ""
    For each character in text:
        Let lowercase_char be convert_character_to_lowercase with char as character
        Set result to result plus lowercase_char
    Return result

Process called "substring" that takes text as String and start as Integer and end as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract substring from text with bounds checking
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let safe_start be maximum of 0 and minimum of start and text_length
    Let safe_end be maximum of safe_start and minimum of end and text_length
    
    Let result be ""
    For i from safe_start to safe_end minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with text as text and index as i
        Set result to result plus char
    
    Return result

Process called "replace_string" that takes text as String and old_substring as String and new_substring as String returns String:
    Note: Replace all occurrences of old_substring with new_substring in text
    If length of old_substring is equal to 0:
        Return text
    
    Let result be ""
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let old_length be length of old_substring
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than text_length:
        Let found_match be true
        If i plus old_length is greater than text_length:
            Set found_match to false
        Otherwise:
            For j from 0 to old_length minus 1:
                Let text_char be character_at with text as text and index as i plus j
                Let old_char be character_at with text as old_substring and index as j
                If text_char is not equal to old_char:
                    Set found_match to false
                    Break
        
        If found_match:
            Set result to result plus new_substring
            Set i to i plus old_length
        Otherwise:
            Let current_char be character_at with text as text and index as i
            Set result to result plus current_char
            Set i to i plus 1
    
    Return result

Process called "is_string" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if value is a string type using type introspection
    Let value_type be get_value_type with value as value
    Return value_type is equal to "string"
:End Note

Note: Low-level Configuration Operations (Implementation-dependent)
Process called "interpolate_configuration_string" that takes template as String and context as Dictionary[String, String] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Advanced configuration string interpolation with variable substitution and nested references
    Try:
        Let result be template
        Let interpolation_depth be 0
        Let max_depth be 10
        Let has_changes be true
        
        Note: Iterative interpolation to handle nested references
        While has_changes and interpolation_depth is less than max_depth:
            Set has_changes to false
            Set interpolation_depth to interpolation_depth plus 1
            
            Note: Find all interpolation patterns ${variable} or #{expression}
            Let i be 0
            Let processed_result be ""
            
            While i is less than length of result:
                Let char be character_at with text as result and index as i
                
                Note: Check for interpolation start patterns
                If char is equal to "$" and i plus 1 is less than length of result:
                    Let next_char be character_at with text as result and index as i plus 1
                    If next_char is equal to "{":
                        Note: Find closing brace
                        Let brace_end be find_closing_brace with text as result and start as i plus 2
                        
                        If brace_end is greater than 0:
                            Let variable_name be substring with text as result and start as i plus 2 and end as brace_end
                            Let substitution_result be substitute_configuration_variable with:
                                variable_name as variable_name
                                context as context
                                configuration as configuration
                            
                            If substitution_result.success:
                                Set processed_result to processed_result plus substitution_result.value
                                Set has_changes to true
                                Set i to brace_end plus 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Note: Keep original pattern if substitution fails
                                Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                                Set i to i plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Malformed interpolation pattern
                            Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                            Set i to i plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                        Set i to i plus 1
                Otherwise if char is equal to "#" and i plus 1 is less than length of result:
                    Let next_char be character_at with text as result and index as i plus 1
                    If next_char is equal to "{":
                        Note: Expression interpolation (advanced feature)
                        Let brace_end be find_closing_brace with text as result and start as i plus 2
                        
                        If brace_end is greater than 0:
                            Let expression be substring with text as result and start as i plus 2 and end as brace_end
                            Let evaluation_result be evaluate_configuration_expression with:
                                expression as expression
                                context as context
                                configuration as configuration
                            
                            If evaluation_result.success:
                                Set processed_result to processed_result plus evaluation_result.value as String
                                Set has_changes to true
                                Set i to brace_end plus 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                                Set i to i plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                            Set i to i plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                        Set i to i plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set processed_result to processed_result plus char
                    Set i to i plus 1
            
            Set result to processed_result
        
        If interpolation_depth is equal to max_depth:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "interpolated_value" as template
                "error_message" as "Maximum interpolation depth reached - possible circular reference"
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "interpolated_value" as result
            "interpolation_depth" as interpolation_depth
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "interpolated_value" as template
            "error_message" as "Interpolation exception: " plus error.message

Process called "encrypt_configuration_value" that takes value as Any and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Encrypt sensitive configuration value
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "encrypted_value" as value as String

Process called "decrypt_configuration_value" that takes config_value as ConfigurationValue and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Decrypt encrypted configuration value
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "decrypted_value" as config_value.value

Process called "apply_value_constraints" that takes value as Any and constraints as Dictionary[String, Any] and key as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply constraints to configuration value
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "apply_custom_validation_rule" that takes value as Any and rule as String and key as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply custom validation rule to configuration value
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "parse_integer_from_string" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse integer from string value with comprehensive validation
    Try:
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with text as value
        
        If length of trimmed_value is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as 0
                "error_message" as "Empty string cannot be parsed as integer"
        
        Note: Check for valid integer format
        Let is_negative be false
        Let start_index be 0
        
        If character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as 0 is equal to "-":
            Set is_negative to true
            Set start_index to 1
        Otherwise if character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as 0 is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        If start_index is equal to length of trimmed_value:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as 0
                "error_message" as "Invalid integer format: only sign character"
        
        Let parsed_value be 0
        For i from start_index to length of trimmed_value minus 1:
            Let char be character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as i
            If not is_digit with char as char:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "value" as 0
                    "error_message" as "Invalid integer format: non-digit character '" plus char plus "'"
            
            Let digit_value be char_to_digit with char as char
            Set parsed_value to parsed_value times 10 plus digit_value
        
        If is_negative:
            Set parsed_value to 0 minus parsed_value
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "value" as parsed_value
            "error_message" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as 0
            "error_message" as "Integer parsing exception: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_float_from_string" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse float from string value with decimal point and scientific notation support
    Try:
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with text as value
        
        If length of trimmed_value is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as 0.0
                "error_message" as "Empty string cannot be parsed as float"
        
        Note: Handle special float values
        If trimmed_value is equal to "NaN" or trimmed_value is equal to "nan":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as get_float_nan
                "error_message" as ""
        
        If trimmed_value is equal to "Infinity" or trimmed_value is equal to "inf":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as get_float_infinity
                "error_message" as ""
        
        If trimmed_value is equal to "-Infinity" or trimmed_value is equal to "-inf":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as get_float_negative_infinity
                "error_message" as ""
        
        Note: Parse standard float format
        Let is_negative be false
        Let start_index be 0
        
        If character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as 0 is equal to "-":
            Set is_negative to true
            Set start_index to 1
        Otherwise if character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as 0 is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        Let integer_part be 0.0
        Let fractional_part be 0.0
        Let decimal_places be 0
        Let found_decimal_point be false
        Let current_index be start_index
        
        Note: Parse integer part and fractional part
        While current_index is less than length of trimmed_value:
            Let char be character_at with text as trimmed_value and index as current_index
            
            If char is equal to ".":
                If found_decimal_point:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "success" as false
                        "value" as 0.0
                        "error_message" as "Multiple decimal points in float"
                Set found_decimal_point to true
            Otherwise if is_digit with char as char:
                Let digit_value be char_to_digit with char as char
                If found_decimal_point:
                    Set decimal_places to decimal_places plus 1
                    Set fractional_part to fractional_part plus digit_value divided by power of 10 and decimal_places
                Otherwise:
                    Set integer_part to integer_part times 10 plus digit_value
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "value" as 0.0
                    "error_message" as "Invalid float format: unexpected character '" plus char plus "'"
            
            Set current_index to current_index plus 1
        
        Let parsed_value be integer_part plus fractional_part
        If is_negative:
            Set parsed_value to 0.0 minus parsed_value
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "value" as parsed_value
            "error_message" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as 0.0
            "error_message" as "Float parsing exception: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_boolean_from_string" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse boolean from string with support for multiple true/false representations
    Try:
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with text as value
        Let lowercase_value be lowercase with text as trimmed_value
        
        If length of lowercase_value is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as false
                "error_message" as "Empty string cannot be parsed as boolean"
        
        Note: True values
        If lowercase_value is equal to "true" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "yes" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "on" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "1" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "enabled" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "active":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as true
                "error_message" as ""
        
        Note: False values
        If lowercase_value is equal to "false" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "no" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "off" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "0" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "disabled" or 
           lowercase_value is equal to "inactive":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as false
                "error_message" as ""
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as false
            "error_message" as "Invalid boolean format: '" plus trimmed_value plus "'. Expected: true, false, yes, no, on, off, 1, 0, enabled, disabled, active, inactive"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as false
            "error_message" as "Boolean parsing exception: " plus error.message

Process called "log_configuration_event" that takes config_id as String and event_type as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Note: Log configuration event for audit trail
    Return None

Process called "log_configuration_change" that takes config_id as String and change as ConfigurationChange returns None:
    Note: Log configuration change for audit trail
    Return None

Process called "notify_configuration_change" that takes configuration as Configuration and change as ConfigurationChange returns None:
    Note: Notify listeners of configuration change
    Return None

Process called "load_from_remote_source" that takes source as ConfigurationSource and configuration as Configuration and options as ConfigurationOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Load configuration from remote source (HTTP, database, etc.)
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "error", "error_message" as "Remote sources not implemented", "values" as dictionary containing

Note: Additional Helper Functions for Configuration Processing
Process called "find_closing_brace" that takes text as String and start as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find matching closing brace for interpolation patterns
    Let brace_count be 1
    Let i be start
    
    While i is less than length of text and brace_count is greater than 0:
        Let char be character_at with text as text and index as i
        If char is equal to "{":
            Set brace_count to brace_count plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "}":
            Set brace_count to brace_count minus 1
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    If brace_count is equal to 0:
        Return i minus 1
    Return -1

Process called "substitute_configuration_variable" that takes variable_name as String and context as Dictionary[String, String] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Substitute a configuration variable with its value from context
    Try:
        Note: Check direct context lookup first
        If context contains variable_name:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as context[variable_name]
        
        Note: Check configuration values
        If configuration.values contains variable_name:
            Let config_value be configuration.values[variable_name]
            If not config_value.sensitive:  Note: Don't expose sensitive values in interpolation
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as true
                    "value" as config_value.value as String
        
        Note: Check for nested variable access (e.g., "env.PATH")
        If variable_name contains ".":
            Let dot_index be find_character_index with text as variable_name and char as "."
            Let prefix be substring with text as variable_name and start as 0 and end as dot_index
            Let suffix be substring with text as variable_name and start as dot_index plus 1 and end as length of variable_name
            
            If prefix is equal to "env" and context contains "env." plus suffix:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as true
                    "value" as context["env." plus suffix]
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Variable not found: " plus variable_name
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Variable substitution exception: " plus error.message

Process called "evaluate_configuration_expression" that takes expression as String and context as Dictionary[String, String] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Evaluate configuration expressions with support for variables, operators, functions, and conditionals
    Try:
        Let trimmed_expression be trim_whitespace with text as expression
        
        Note: Handle empty or whitespace-only expressions
        If length of trimmed_expression is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "value" as ""
                "error_message" as ""
        
        Note: Check for simple variable references first (optimization)
        If is_simple_variable with expression as trimmed_expression:
            Let variable_result be resolve_variable_reference with:
                variable_name as trimmed_expression
                context as context
                configuration as configuration
            Return variable_result
        
        Note: Parse and evaluate complex expressions
        Let tokens be tokenize_expression with expression as trimmed_expression
        If length of tokens is equal to 0:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as ""
                "error_message" as "Empty expression after tokenization"
        
        Note: Build expression tree from tokens
        Let expression_tree be parse_expression_tokens with tokens as tokens
        If expression_tree is None:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "value" as ""
                "error_message" as "Failed to parse expression syntax"
        
        Note: Evaluate the parsed expression tree
        Let evaluation_result be evaluate_expression_tree with:
            tree as expression_tree
            context as context
            configuration as configuration
        
        Return evaluation_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Expression evaluation exception: " plus error.message

Process called "is_simple_variable" that takes expression as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if expression is just a simple variable name without operators or functions
    Let length be length of expression
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return false
    
    Note: Check for operators, parentheses, quotes, or function calls
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with text as expression and index as i
        If char is equal to "+" or char is equal to "-" or char is equal to "*" or char is equal to "/" or char is equal to "%" or char is equal to "(" or char is equal to ")" or char is equal to "\"" or char is equal to "'" or char is equal to "=" or char is equal to "!" or char is equal to "<" or char is equal to ">" or char is equal to "&" or char is equal to "|" or char is equal to "?" or char is equal to ":":
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "tokenize_expression" that takes expression as String returns List[ExpressionToken]:
    Note: Tokenize configuration expression into operators, operands, functions, and literals
    Let tokens be list containing
    Let current_token be ""
    Let in_string_literal be false
    Let string_delimiter be ""
    Let length be length of expression
    
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with text as expression and index as i
        
        Note: Handle string literals
        If in_string_literal:
            If char is equal to string_delimiter:
                Let string_value be current_token
                Add to tokens: create_string_literal_token with value as string_value
                Let current_token be ""
                Let in_string_literal be false
                Let string_delimiter be ""
            Otherwise:
                Let current_token be current_token plus char
        Otherwise:
            Note: Start of string literal
            If char is equal to "\"" or char is equal to "'":
                If length of current_token is greater than 0:
                    Add to tokens: create_identifier_token with name as current_token
                    Let current_token be ""
                Let in_string_literal be true
                Let string_delimiter be char
            Note: Operators and delimiters
            Otherwise if char is equal to "+" or char is equal to "-" or char is equal to "*" or char is equal to "/" or char is equal to "%" or char is equal to "=" or char is equal to "!" or char is equal to "<" or char is equal to ">" or char is equal to "(" or char is equal to ")" or char is equal to "," or char is equal to "?" or char is equal to ":":
                If length of current_token is greater than 0:
                    Add to tokens: create_identifier_token with name as current_token
                    Let current_token be ""
                Add to tokens: create_operator_token with operator as char
            Note: Whitespace
            Otherwise if char is equal to " " or char is equal to "\t" or char is equal to "\n" or char is equal to "\r":
                If length of current_token is greater than 0:
                    Add to tokens: create_identifier_token with name as current_token
                    Let current_token be ""
            Note: Regular characters
            Otherwise:
                Let current_token be current_token plus char
    
    Note: Handle remaining token
    If length of current_token is greater than 0:
        If in_string_literal:
            Add to tokens: create_error_token with message as "Unterminated string literal"
        Otherwise:
            Add to tokens: create_identifier_token with name as current_token
    
    Return tokens

Process called "parse_expression_tokens" that takes tokens as List[ExpressionToken] returns ExpressionTree:
    Note: Parse tokens into expression tree using recursive descent parsing
    If length of tokens is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Note: Handle simple single-token cases
    If length of tokens is equal to 1:
        Let token be get_at with list as tokens and index as 0
        If token.type is equal to "identifier":
            Return create_variable_node with name as token.value
        Otherwise if token.type is equal to "string_literal":
            Return create_literal_node with value as token.value and data_type as "string"
        Otherwise if token.type is equal to "number_literal":
            Return create_literal_node with value as token.value and data_type as "number"
        Otherwise:
            Return None
    
    Note: Parse conditional expressions (ternary operator)
    Let conditional_tree be parse_conditional_expression with tokens as tokens
    Return conditional_tree

Process called "evaluate_expression_tree" that takes tree as ExpressionTree and context as Dictionary[String, String] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Recursively evaluate expression tree nodes
    If tree is None:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Null expression tree"
    
    Note: Handle different node types
    If tree.node_type is equal to "literal":
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "value" as tree.value
            "error_message" as ""
    
    Otherwise if tree.node_type is equal to "variable":
        Let variable_result be resolve_variable_reference with:
            variable_name as tree.name
            context as context
            configuration as configuration
        Return variable_result
    
    Otherwise if tree.node_type is equal to "binary_operation":
        Let left_result be evaluate_expression_tree with:
            tree as tree.left
            context as context
            configuration as configuration
        
        If left_result["success"] is equal to false:
            Return left_result
        
        Let right_result be evaluate_expression_tree with:
            tree as tree.right
            context as context
            configuration as configuration
        
        If right_result["success"] is equal to false:
            Return right_result
        
        Let operation_result be evaluate_binary_operation with:
            operator as tree.operator
            left_value as left_result["value"]
            right_value as right_result["value"]
        
        Return operation_result
    
    Otherwise if tree.node_type is equal to "function_call":
        Let function_result be evaluate_function_call with:
            function_name as tree.function_name
            arguments as tree.arguments
            context as context
            configuration as configuration
        
        Return function_result
    
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Unknown expression tree node type: " plus tree.node_type

Process called "find_character_index" that takes text as String and char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Find first occurrence of character in text
    For i from 0 to length of text minus 1:
        Let current_char be character_at with text as text and index as i
        If current_char is equal to char:
            Return i
    Return -1

Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace from string
    Let start be 0
    Let end be length of text
    
    Note: Find first non-whitespace character
    While start is less than end:
        Let char be character_at with text as text and index as start
        If not is_whitespace with char as char:
            Break
        Set start to start plus 1
    
    Note: Find last non-whitespace character
    While end is greater than start:
        Let char be character_at with text as text and index as end minus 1
        If not is_whitespace with char as char:
            Break
        Set end to end minus 1
    
    Return substring with text as text and start as start and end as end

Process called "is_whitespace" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is whitespace (space, tab, newline, carriage return)
    Return char is equal to " " or char is equal to "\t" or char is equal to "\n" or char is equal to "\r"

Process called "is_digit" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is a decimal digit
    Return char is equal to "0" or char is equal to "1" or char is equal to "2" or 
           char is equal to "3" or char is equal to "4" or char is equal to "5" or 
           char is equal to "6" or char is equal to "7" or char is equal to "8" or 
           char is equal to "9"

Process called "char_to_digit" that takes char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert digit character to integer value
    Match char:
        When "0": Return 0
        When "1": Return 1
        When "2": Return 2
        When "3": Return 3
        When "4": Return 4
        When "5": Return 5
        When "6": Return 6
        When "7": Return 7
        When "8": Return 8
        When "9": Return 9
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "character_at" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get character at specific index in string (bounds checking needed)
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of text:
        Return ""
    Note: Implementation should return actual character at index
    Return ""

Process called "copy_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Note: Create shallow copy of list
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Add item to result
    Return result

