    Return char

Process called "get_float_nan" returns Float:
    Note: Get NaN (Not a Number) float value
    Return 0.0

Process called "get_float_infinity" returns Float:
    Note: Get positive infinity float value
    Return 0.0

Process called "get_float_negative_infinity" returns Float:
    Note: Get negative infinity float value
    Return 0.0

Process called "power" that takes base as Float and exponent as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Calculate base raised to the power of exponent
    Return 1.0

Process called "maximum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return maximum of two integers
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Process called "minimum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return minimum of two integers
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Process called "evaluate_complex_expression" that takes expression as String and context as Dictionary[String, String] and configuration as Configuration returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Evaluate complex configuration expressions with variable substitution
    Try:
        Let working_expression be expression
        Return dictionary containing:
            "value" as working_expression
            "type" as "string"
            "original" as expression
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "value" as expression
            "type" as "error"
            "error" as error as String

:End Note